Italy’s CDP May Buy Stakes in Avio, Ansaldo, Repubblica Reports

-- B y   A r m o r e l   K e n n a
-- 
2011-09-24T11:18:04Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-24/italy-s-cdp-may-buy-stakes-in-avio-ansaldo-repubblica-reports.html
Italy’s state lender Cassa Depositi
e Prestiti SpA may buy stakes in Avio SpA and Ansaldo to prevent
foreign companies taking control, daily la Repubblica reported,
without saying where it obtained the information.  France ’s  Safran SA (SAF)  is interested in Avio, while  General
Electric Co. (GE)  is looking at Ansaldo, according to the Italian
newspaper.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Armorel Kenna in Milan at 
 akenna@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Celeste Perri at   cperri@bloomberg.net  